# API Response Serialization

## Rule

All JSON keys in successful `data` payloads and error `details` objects must be **snake_case**.

## Implementation

- `toSnakeCaseDeep()` in `src/shared/utils/snake-case.ts` recursively converts keys
- `sendSuccess()` / `sendCreated()` in `src/shared/utils/response.ts` apply conversion automatically
- `error-handler.ts` snake_cases `AppError.details`

## Authoring code

Write camelCase in services and mappers; never duplicate snake_case field names in application logic.

```typescript
// ✅ Service returns camelCase
return { totalUsers, recentActivity, pageSize: query.pageSize };

// ✅ Controller
return sendSuccess(res, result);

// ❌ Manual response bypassing helper
res.json({ data: { access_token: token } });

// ❌ Hand-built snake_case in services
return { access_token: token };
```

## Tests

Add or update unit tests when changing serialization (see `src/tests/snake-case.test.ts`).
